This is the notes for updatingAdocument

We are going to learn how to update documents in a MongoDB database

We start off by creating a new function called updateCourse

there are 2 ways to update a document the first approach is called 
Query first
So we would find the document using: 
findById
modify its properties 
save the document 

This approach is useful if we recieve input from the client and we need to make sure it is a valid operation 
 

The second approach is called update first
// update directly
// optionally get the updated document

For this example we will use the first approach then the second